DATA
Per her outside lab work, her albumin on April 14, 2010, was low at 3.0 with a total protein at 5.1.  Other lab results discussed above.
IMPRESSION
#1 Likely ascending colon cancer
Discussed with Mrs. Prime and her family that this would be a big operation if she undergoes a right hemicolectomy.  There is some discrepancy whether this is actually in the descending colon or what is the exact situation as she had prior colon surgery.  It may be important to do another colonoscopy as there was no tattooing performed, but I will let her meet with one of our surgeons, and we will review her outside CT-scan first to see if this really needs to be performed as this would be quite difficult for her as she is frail and has limited mobility at this time.  We will get a CEA.  I discussed with the family that if this could be done partially laparoscopically, she would likely be hospitalized three to five days if everything else goes smooth or five to seven days for an open operation.  I do agree with them that she would likely need skilled nursing facility placement following surgery if we end up proceeding this route.  The family and the patient had a long discussion, and they would like to proceed with evaluation for definitive surgery for her but will make their final decision following her preoperative evaluation and seeing Cardiology.  I discussed with her if our outside review of her CT-scan is concerning for possible liver mets, we may need an abdominal ultrasound.  I did discuss with the family if they decided not to proceed with a large surgery to definitively treat this, at times we can put in a colonic stent, although on the right-side I am not sure whether this is easily feasible, or sometimes we divert with just a diverting ileostomy so that she would not obstruct.  They asked specific questions about additional options instead of the large abdominal surgery if she is not medically able to undergo this.  We will also get chest x-ray.
#2 Coronary artery disease
For preoperative clearance we will send to Cardiology.  She has not had a recent cardiac evaluation.  We will get a baseline EKG.  Give her an updated prescription for nitroglycerin.
