12.  Osteoporosis.
13.  Degenerative joint disease of the cervical spine and lumbar spine.
14.  Carotid stenosis.  She has had multiple carotid endarterectomies, twice to the right-side and once to the left. An updated carotid ultrasound in February 007 which did not reveal significant restenosis.
15.  Sleep disorder.  She had been on Ambien, but this was stopped in the hospital, and she has been taking Tylenol at night to help her sleep which has been working.
16.  Urinary incontinence.  She wears Depends as she has issues with urinary incontinence.  She has had problems with urinary tract infections and is on prophylactic nitrofurantoin.  It has been over six-months since she had an infection.  She is not symptomatic currently.
17.  Fecal incontinence.  Discussed above.
